# {{.Name}}

Custom kernel LLM tester — swap CUDA/Triton/FlashAttention backends and benchmark.

Switch backends: `--kernel torch` / `--kernel triton` / `--kernel cuda` / `--flash`

## Quick Start

```bash
make setup
make train-debug
```

## Make Targets

```bash
# Training
make train              # Default backend ({{.KernelBackend}})
make train-debug        # Small model, quick test
make train-compiled     # torch.compile
make train-triton       # Triton kernels (GPU)
make train-cuda         # CUDA kernels (GPU, run make build-cuda first)
make train-flash        # FlashAttention (GPU)

# Profiling
make profile            # PyTorch Profiler
make nsys               # Nsight Systems
make ncu                # Nsight Compute
make perf-stat          # perf hardware counters
make perf-record        # perf CPU sampling
make perf-flame         # flame graph
make tensorboard        # view logs

# Benchmarking
make benchmark

# Other
make generate
make kernels            # list registered backends
make build-cuda         # compile CUDA kernels
make clean
```

## Structure

```
kernels/          Registry + Factory pattern, Triton + CUDA kernels
profiling/        PyTorch Profiler, Nsight, perf, benchmarks
src/              GPT model, training, generation
config.py         GPTConfig
main.py           CLI entry point
```
